[1] Diarrhea - Iraq
Date: Sun 24 Feb 2008
Source: UN Office for the Coordination of Humanitarian Affairs (OCHA),
ReliefWeb, WHO report [edited]
<http://www.reliefweb.int/rw/RWB.NSF/db900SID/KKAA-7CL8LY?OpenDocument&rc=3&cc=irq>


Week of 18-24 Feb 2008
----------------------
- out of the 893 reporting sites, 829 sites (93 per cent) reported data on
AWD [acute watery diarrhea] and water quality.
- all 19 Directorates of Health (DoHs) submitted reports, however Anbar DoH
report was limited to Falluja hospital; data received from Anbar, and
Diyala DoHs was not sufficient in regards to monitoring completeness of
reporting. Excellent progress in reporting from Sulaymaniyah.
- in total, 6426 AWD cases were reported, but none of the 3167 samples
cultured were positive for cholera.
- Baghdad Resafa: reporting of both diarrhea cases and stool samples tested
is showing improvement week by week.
- Basra: Basra remains one of the most regularly reporting DoHs. 434 cases
of AWD were reported. None of the 304 stool samples tested were
culture-positive for cholera.
- Diyala : 54 diarrhea cases reported, 47 stool samples were collected for
culture. Although AWD surveillance is slowly progressing, it is still one
of the weakest AWD surveillance in the country.
- Kirkuk: 235 cases of AWD were reported. None of the 82 samples cultured
were positive for cholera. For the 10th week in a row no cholera case have
been reported from Kirkuk.
- Missan: 80 cases of AWD were reported (compared to 190 last week) (there
is a definite typing mistake in the number of stool samples cultured for VC
[_Vibrio cholerae_] (399) which is almost 5 times the number of diarrhea
cases. Surveillance staff are requested to check the consistency of data
before submission to CDC/Baghdad.
- Mosul: 564 AWD cases reported, none of the 271 stool samples cultured
were positive for cholera.
- Najaf: 478 AWD cases reported, none of the 392 stool samples cultured
were positive for cholera.
- Sulaymaniyah: 595 AWD cases were reported. None of the 125 samples
cultured were positive for cholera. Week by week reporting is improving in
Sulaymaniyah.
- Thiqar, Muthana, Tikrit, and Babylon: 972 cases of AWD were reported.
None of the 450 stool samples cultured were positive for cholera.
- total new confirmed cholera cases: 0

--
