[5] Cholera - Uganda (Arua)
Date: Tue 4 Mar 2008
Source: AllAfrica, The Monitor (Kampala) report [edited]
<http://allafrica.com/stories/200803041185.html>


A total of 6 people died of cholera in River Oli division in Arua district.
The most affected areas include Kenya, Tanganyika, and Pangisha. Latest
statistics show that 70 cases have been reported since the outbreak began
in January 2008.

The assistant town clerk, Mr Alfred Oyo, said the division lacks funds for
purchasing basic facilities to contain the spread. He attributed the
outbreak to dense population, poor waste disposal, and blocked drainage.
The health team has now embarked on a sensitisation exercise to communities
to have better hygiene and sanitation as a measure to stem the spread

[byline: Proscovia Acan, Warom Felix Okello]

--
